  "texts": [
    "In fact, OpenAI used outsourced Kenyan workers earning less than USD 2.00 per hour to label \"toxic content\" (PERRIGO, 2023).",
    "Limitations include the occasional generation of plausible-sounding but incorrect or nonsensical answers.",
    "The model is sensitive to input phrasing variations and may be excessively verbose, with biases from training data contributing to these issues.",
    "Additionally, the model tends to guess user intent instead of asking clarifying questions for ambiguous queries.",
    "Efforts have been made to address inappropriate requests, but the model may still respond to harmful instructions or exhibit biased behavior."
